bugs_active |id, severity, status, title, file, line, reproducible_by, created_at, updated_at, valid|
    md_diag_tuple_element_corruption, P1, open, "Interpreter corrupts .2/.3 element access on (i64,i64,text,text) tuple arrays -- text fields return garbage pointers, trim().len() returns -1", src/lib/editor/services/md_diagnostics.spl, 593, for item in tuple_array: item.2 returns <value:0x..> instead of text; worked around with MdDiagLinkRef struct, 2026-04-14, 2026-04-14, true
    md_slugify_string_corruption, P1, open, markdown_slugify returns heap-state-dependent corrupted slugs in interpreter -- same input gave l-h / l-a / a / section across call sites in one run; cross-module text args sometimes arrive empty or truncated, src/lib/common/markdown/utilities.spl, 27, probe calling markdown_slugify with literal Alpha from different frames returns different values; worked around in md_wiki heading transclusion via exact trimmed-title compare and case-insensitive title fallback, 2026-06-12, 2026-06-12, true
    sdn_reader_utf8_byte_indexing, P2, fixed, SDN bug_db reader crashes with string index out of bounds on multibyte UTF-8 in quoted field -- byte length used as char index, src/app/cli, 0, bug-add with em-dash in an existing bugs_active title fails: string index out of bounds index is 376 but length is 376; also bug-add then fails with q-operator-on-nil after parse succeeds, 2026-06-12, 2026-06-14, true
    wal_disk_replay_blank_row, P0, fixed, DBFS MetaStore WAL disk replay dropped all field data -- journal serialization collapsed every op to an empty CHECKPOINT so replayed rows came back blank, src/lib/nogc_sync_mut/db/dbfs_engine/meta_store.spl, 113, write_inode then reopen MetaStore.open and replay_journal returned blank rows; raw .meta.wal showed 1~CHECKPOINT~~ empty payload instead of 1~INODE_WRITE~..fields; fixed by replacing broken op is MetaOp.Variant discrimination with match, 2026-06-14, 2026-06-14, true
    interp_qualified_enum_is_payload_variant, P1, open, Interpreter: x is MetaOp.Variant evaluates false even for a freshly constructed payload-carrying enum variant -- forces if-is chains to fall through to else; use match instead, src/compiler, 0, enum E with A(x) B; val a=E.A(x:5); (a is E.A) returns false while match a case E.A(x) binds correctly; root cause of wal_disk_replay_blank_row, 2026-06-14, 2026-06-14, true
    vulkan_per_primitive_submit_wait_throughput, P2, open, Vulkan per-primitive submit_and_wait caps GUI render at 4ms per op so widget frames fall far below 200 per sec, src/lib/gc_async_mut/gpu/engine2d/backend_vulkan.spl, 494, SIMPLE_EXECUTION_MODE=interpret loop clear+K draw_rect_filled VulkanBackend 1280x720: 32 widgets=7/sec 128=1/sec, 2026-04-14, 2026-04-14, true
    vulkan_present_readback_perpixel_simple_loop, P2, open, "VulkanBackend present host readback runs two per-pixel Simple loops, 134s for one 1280x720 frame under classic interpreter", src/lib/gc_async_mut/gpu/engine2d/backend_vulkan.spl, 622, SIMPLE_EXECUTION_MODE=interpret time one present VulkanBackend 1280x720: 134653750 us, 2026-04-14, 2026-04-14, true


